news.title: Sobha's profit up 51% to Rs 32.7 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income rose marginally to Rs 697.5 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 696.3 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.Total income rose marginally to Rs 697.5 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 696.3 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Chinese builders' shares up on reports they may have more access to funds
news.para: Regulatory curbs on borrowing have driven China's property sector into a liquidity crisis, highlighted by Evergrande , the world's most indebted property firm.

news.title: Britain's Landsec to invest $2 billion in mixed-use spaces bet
news.para: Britain's largest commercial landlord is aiming to increase the share of mixed-use properties in its business to 25% from the current 8% through projects that will build some 7,000 homes and three million square feet of office space, Chief Executive Mark Allan told reporters on a conference call.

news.title: Brookfield REIT posts Rs 59.7 crore net income in Q3 FY22
news.para: The Canadian alternative investment major Brookfield Asset Management-backed Biret was listed in February 2021 after a Rs 3,800-crore public issue which was oversubscribed 8-times.

news.title: Kerala: Only 63% applications under Life Mission verified so far
news.para: Even among the verified, only 64.5% of the applications were found eligible for processing. Of the total number of applications received, only 5,83,676 applications were verified till date and 3,76,701 were found to be eligible.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's net profit dips 4% to Rs 84 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: However, its revenue from operations climbed 18.03 per cent to Rs 914.34 crore during the quarter under review, as against Rs 774.64 crore in the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.

news.title: Brigade, GIC to buy 5.5 acres property in Chennai from TVS for Rs 550 crore
news.para: Nirupa Shankar, executive director at Brigade Enterprises, confirmed that the group has come to an understanding to purchase the property from a TVS Group company.

news.title: Chintels India to conduct structural audit of Chintels Paradiso
news.para: Police have booked the builder and the construction contractor for negligence while the district administration has ordered an inquiry into the matter, according to officials.

news.title: TUDA to raise Rs 300 crore by auctioning 145 acres of Surappakasam lands near Tirupati
news.para: The prestigious township has been named as Padmavathi Nagar TUDA township which is just 10 kms away from the Tirupati airport and 11km away from the railway station.

news.title: India Cements reports standalone net profit of Rs 3.30 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income on standalone basis stood at Rs 1,114.22 crore as against Rs 1,162.91 crore registered same period last fiscal. Total income for the nine month period on standalone basis ending December 31, 2021, grew to Rs 3,333.11 crore from Rs 2,998.68 crore registered same period last fiscal.

news.title: Sale of residential and commercial sites on freehold basis in Chandigarh
news.para: With this move, sale of hundreds of commercial and residential properties of all the departments of the Chandigarh administration, namely Chandigarh Housing Board, municipal corporation and estate office, will be started through e-auction.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal guesthouses flourish as DTCP slows down action
news.para: After making tall claims about elaborate survey and action plans against 1,000 illegal guesthouses in the city, the department has failed to act while the residents in these colonies are facing tough time due to additional burden on infrastructure and safety and security concerns.

news.title: SDMC Budget: Proposal to hike property tax rejected
news.para: The SDMC on Thursday also announced that tax on one property will be exempted for native residents living in rural areas of south Delhi.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso: Death toll rises to two; builder booked
news.para: Police have booked the builder of Chintels Paradiso, a residential complex, and the construction contractor for negligence, while the district administration has ordered an inquiry into the matter, they said.

news.title: Kochi civic body plans 15% cess on property tax
news.para: The corporation is head-deep in a financial crisis which has evolved over the past several years. The local body owes the contractors a huge amount and lack of funds has impacted the implementation of many projects.
